{
  "name": "RPlog_Local_Law",
  "title": "Local Law",
  "summary": "Commander Jonas, in full uniform for once, meets with Commander Valerius and the visiting intelligence officer Rainer at a Corellian military base to debrief local CorSec officers, Major Peny and Captain Durjan, about a covert broadcast operation. The interview sours as Durjan abruptly seals the room, guns down Major Peny, and reveals himself as a traitor intent on taking the Imperials hostage for an exchange. A vicious close-quarters brawl erupts, with Jonas, Valerius, and the wry Rainer trading blows and blaster fire with the determined Durjan until the stormtrooper Brek Halsmer blasts through the door to turn the tide. The corrupt captain is beaten down and shackled, and the officers grimly agree he must be treated as a hostile interrogation subject. With the fight won, the battered group trades dark humor and drinks amid the wrecked office, toasting the end of the bloody affair.",
